< review>
Both me and my husband have been patients here for 4 years and always had great experience. Dr. Young is the best! She does my exams every year and she is always sweet and attentive to details. She takes time to explain me everything and answers all my questions. Other staff members are great too! Also I‚Äôd like to note that the place itself looks nice and modern, all exam rooms look clean, pretty good selection of frames as well. And they take great precautions during the pandemic: they ask to sanitize your hands upon arrival, they let patients in and out from different doors to minimize unnecessary contact. All equipment is well sanitized before every use. Patients are allowed to try on different frames but frames are returned back only after being sanitized. Thank you for doing great job guys!< /review>

<resp>None< /resp><Name>Celeste Zanabria<//Name>< time>
1564370835477<//time>
<pics>None< /pics><user>100919151410206665453</user>< text>
Long story short: come see Dr. Chatwani! Coming from someone who has been to 4 other Optometrists prior to her, she's the best! And I've been coming to her practice for 13+ years aka half my life! PLUS!! she's the Oakland Athletics Optometrists....what's NOT to like!?

I absolutely love coming to Tri-City Optometry! I have been coming to see Dr. Chatwani ever since she took over the business location from the previous Optometry that was in Newark....so about 13-14 years! I never miss a year without stopping by to get my vision checked by Dr. Chatwani and catching up. She knows my family and always remembers to ask about all of them. Last year, I changed vision insurance and sadly, it only covers getting my vision checked AT Kaiser. There is no one else I trust to get my vision right other than her! I decided to pay the exam fee out of pocket (thank you FSA! Its $150 btw) and  attend my yearly exam. Dr. C took the time to get my vision correct, there was a lot of back and forth trying to her my right eye with the best prescription possible. She doesn't like to double check - she triple checks! Thankfully, only my right eye was an issue and was the culprit for the sinus headaches and vision issues I was experiencing.

Afterward, you get to pick out glasses if you'd like - or you can bring a pair and just have the prescription updated. I picked out two pairs of glasses - a D&G and Ragbone pair - which I will post when I go pick them up. Also, if you have a Flexible Spending Account and have a balance remaining before the end of the year/spending year, they will cash out the FSA and give you a gift card to spend it on frames, sunglasses, etc.! It gives you another year to use and save it for what you'd like.

New location is amazing btw. If you went to the previous one in Newark, it was nice and cozy and felt like home - but now it's so open, and spacious...which means so many MORE frames to choose from!<//text>

<Text>I had several good experiences with Dynamic Air Services and definitely recommend you try this company for yourself - here are a few reasons why:

Most important, I discovered that all employees at Dynamic, from customer service on the phone, repair and estimate technicians, to the installers all were kind, professional, and informative before, during, and after every service and installation.

Several other companies made assumptions and bids without even inspecting the coil, condenser, or furnace. Just because something is old, doesn't mean it is broken and needs to be replaced. While Dynamic did comment that my HVAC system was more than 10 years old, they tested and diagnosed all parts then provided reasonable repair and replace estimates.

While I received several scared tactic estimates from other local and national firms, Dynamic was the only company to provide clear and concise information based upon facts with 1) documented proof and 2) independent verifiable information.

For example, on the repair side of the coin, I received multiple quotes stating my freon was low and needed to be filled or topped off with a cost ranging from $150 to $675. The Dynamic rep showed me the actual levels in my current unit, explained the min and max levels, and I was able to independently verify online prices as well as the pros and cons of "topping off" the levels. The freon levels were better than good and did not need any servicing.

I'm not a Subject Matter Expert (SME) in all things HVAC, therefore I need to trust the company I select. And while I could have used my current HVAC for another 5 or more years, I opted for a new Lennox system with a wifi thermostat.

P.S. the cat in the pic was purchased separately.<//Text>< UserId.>

<review>The details matter when buying something as expensive as a home HVAC system. Dynamic is a company that, over 3 years of doing business with them, seems to always sweat the details and get them right!

After interviewing over 10 HVAC companies, I selected Dynamic and I have been so happy I did! The owner Bill came out to do the initial scoping of the work and this is one area that made all the difference. The 9 other companies all said some variation of, "I've been doing this for years, you need a x-Ton AC Unit" without doing any heat load calculations. I asked them all, and all refused, except Bill. And after spending the hour doing them, he realized for my house the issue wasn't the AC compressor size, it was DUCTING. His quote came back in the middle of all the quotes, but included a lot of effort to get my ducting right (my house was built in 1968 and had no AC). Of course it came with a Honeywell smart thermostat. They also recommended a variable speed blower motor so that we could run the house fan at low speed 24/7 to keep upstairs and downstairs more balanced. The initial install took 2 days, but they came back on the 3rd to make it look perfect and to help eliminate noise from the condensation pump.

We did sign up for the 2x/year service (winter to check heater, summer to check AC) for the first 3 years which is key to getting the full 10 year warranty.

Now that we've had the system for 3+years, I'm SUPER HAPPY.  Kelly and the rest of the office staff have always been very professional. The technicians that have come to our home have always been polite, on time, professional and tidy. The most recent tech, Jeff, was **AMAZING** . He was actually able to work on the furnace / AC components in the utility closet that is connected to my baby's room, while the baby was sleeping, without waking him up!<//review>< Pics>

<Review>we were out of town for the weekend and on our way home we turned on the AC from our phone App. My husband stated that he looked an hour later and the house hadn't cooled at all. It was very hot and humid, so we figured it would take a little while to cool down. once we got home we realized the although the air was blowing inside it was not cold. We started making callas to get someone out there, we quickly found out that the system was bad and would need replacement.

in our search we ran across Dynamic air services and with all their positive reviews we called them out for a quote. I have to say im very glad we did.....they made an unenjoyable experience painless.

We scheduled an appointment for a quote and John was a pleasure and quite helpful in working around our schedule. prior to our appointment we received updates to our email reminding us of our email as well as notifying us that our technician was on his way with a picture and the techs name.

Our technician was BIll.....I cant say enough good about him and how he explained everything in detail to us. We received 5 different bids to replace our system and pricing was all over the place. Bill took the time to explain what the requirements were by the state and city as well as what they were doing to guarantee the system will be installed to all requirements.....we noticed that the other quotes we received were very vague in regards to the process that is required and quite a few didn't even include permits or any guarantees that the system will pass inspection. WE felt very comfortable that Dynamicwas doing everything the correct way as well as not cutting any corners.

Once we made our decision, we called into the office and John once again was a pleasure to deal with. IT was then that we realized we couldn't get our installation done for about a week and we were in the middle of a heat wave. John let us know that Dynamic offers FREE loaner AC units.....we were blown away. No one offered anything like that. John set our appointment and later that day an employee from Dynamic air came over and set op our temporary AC, this made the wait till our installation much more tolerable.

On the day of the install, they showed up on time as promised and got right to work setting up for the install. It was surprising to see how much care they took in making sure that there was no damage to our home. They had tarps and floor protection laid down so that our carpet and flooring wasn't damaged. They worked very clean and careful. You could see that the team worked very efficiently and showed true pride in their work. As the project was nearing completion we noticed the same care that was shown in setting up the install was used in the clean up. they vacuumd and cleaned and once they were done t was like they were never there.

They spent the time to show us all of the features of the system and make sure that we didn't have any questions before they left. They also included one year of maintenance with the system at no additional charge.

I would highly recommend them for any work as they show a level of professionalism that just isn't common when it comes to contractors.<//Review><pictures>None< /pictures><resp>{'time': 1553558534896, 'text': 'Thanks'}< /resp><gmapID>0x80dce9fbaa9cb09f:0xb1ce92705c52eb12< /gmapID></record>

<user_id>102411545487216108276< /user_id><username>Erica Chuvichien<//username><time>1555136893024<//time>< Rate>
4<//Rate>
< Review>
We heard about this place from people around Merced, so when we had the opportunity to try it while in Le grand we took it. It was damn good!!!! We went back twice in one day!!! Theres not much sitting area and they only take cash. The little liquor store next to them willet you get cash back, but she doesnt charge a flat rate. She charges a fee depending on how much you spend in her liquor store...pretty shady if you ask me. So take cash before you go. Le Grand doesnt have a Chase or BofA around.

You wont be disappointed with the tacos or burritos!!! They were amazing!!! The ladies cooking inside were very nice and friendly!!

Just know that Le Grand is FULL of gang members. Thankfully we didnt encounter any issues. In fact, the people we did encounter at the truck were all very nice people.  Still, tread carefully. Get your food and go.< /Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< Text>
Been wanting to visit this place before we moved out here and...we finally did today! Definitely gonna come back here and try out the other drinks and food items. My husband and I got some delish cold brews but the La Catrina (ice cream concha sandwich) stole our hearts! We got the horchata ice cream inside of a choco concha, with a choc and caramel drizzle and mazapan bits for topping. Always support local!< /Text>

<name>Kim Ly</name>< Review>
Being born and raised in City heights I've seen so much good and bad changes to our neighborhood. Going to Cafeina and talking to the owner Andrew made me feel so proud to have someone who also was born and raised in the neighborhood making a positive impact to the heart of the city. Andrew's story about being formally in the medical field and now really pursuing his passion with his beautiful coffee shop was inspiring! The coffee shop wasn't just aesthetically pleasing but the coffee was amazing. Andrew nailed it with his recipes. I got the mazapan latte over iced with almond milk. It was perfect! Andrew even broke it down what he thought would be best in this drink for me. Great guy, great energy, super kind human and makes you feel so comfortable in his shop. I bought a shirt from the shop as well! I had to support plus the design was super cool! Told all my friends that grew up in that neighborhood to go check him out. We are all business professionals who love to drink coffee and take meetings at coffee shops. What better way to do it in a place where we once learned how to skateboard and ride a bike two blocks away! Thank you Andrew for being a positive influence to our community! Can't wait to come back this week!</Review>

<rate>5<//rate><Text>I was looking to replace my girlfriends Pandora promise ring and wanted a reliable small business to help me. I ended up ordering a 0.52 carat Diamond ring on a beautiful solitaire setting. At first I was reluctant to order from Yadav since I have never been there and I am no where near California to visit their showroom. Wedding band is 6 bezel set diamonds (0.5 carat total weight) on a 3mm rose gold band. Because the main ring is set so low, the wedding band cannot sit flush against it so they designed it in an "interrupted " fashion, meaning there is actually a gap in the wedding band to give it the illusion of sitting flush. I chose to solder the 2 rings together for this reason, so the wedding band would not spin and show the gap. <Review>I am writing this review largely in part due to the amazing customer service I received from Nan. I have never in my life met a customer service associate who is more responsive and helpful than her. Thank you Nan, you are amazing!

Unfortunately, there were a few hiccups when it came to my ring. My fianc√© found Yadav through Rare Carat. Don't get me wrong, I absolutely love my ring. However, there were a couple flaws which should not have passed their quality control when it comes to an engagement ring. I had to send my ring back in for a resize as it was too big. The process to ship the ring back was extremely easy (thanks to Nan) and I was able to receive it back in a week. But when I got it back, I realized that it was crooked and there were two gaps in the ring (as pictured). I had taken a couple pictures before sending it back as well which I was able to show as proof that the gaps happened after the resizing. Thankfully, Yadav agreed to take the ring back and fix the gaps which I was very grateful for, though I was now anxious I would have to ship my ring back a second time and be apart from it for another week. When I got my ring back for the final time (two pictures against white marbled background), the gap on the part of the band with the row of diamonds had been fixed (yay!) But the gap in the middle still remains.

I love my ring so much and don't want to part with it anymore, so I don't mind the gap too much as it is pretty hard to see unless you're extremely close and scrutinizing. I would just think, for such an expensive ring with such a beautiful diamond, you'd hope the quality is 100%.

All in all, amazing customer service but 1 star off for the quality control.< /Review>< Pics>

<Text>I ordered an engagement diamond through this company after seeing the one I liked on Rarecarat and had it shipped to me. Normally I make large purchases like this in person, especially if it was jewelry, so that I can inspect it and don't have to worry about shipping. Luckily, they had detailed descriptions, photos, and 360 video of the diamond itself so I felt confident enough to make the purchase.

Shipping was very very secure as the diamond was wonderfully packaged in its own little metal capsule, in a weighty box, inside shipping bag, inside a medium box, then AGAIN inside a large shipping box. It had multiple layers of protection and there was no way of telling it was a multi thousand dollar diamond inside. It also required signature on delivery.

The customer service was quick to respond if I wanted a refund, exchange, or shipping updates. The only downside was that the shipping took about two weeks.

Fiance absolutely loves the diamond and gets compliments on it all the time. Keep in mind this was a lab grown, 1,63, ideal cut, oval, vvs2, colorless, all for $4300. Robins Brothers wanted $10,000 for an equivalent lab grown diamond.

That is the last taboo, not related to this company. We were skeptical about getting a lab grown and the comments that may come along with it so we went to check out both lab grown and mined diamonds in person. The salesperson laid 3 lab grown and 3 mined in front of us to let us decide which one is which. After feeling confident on our choices we were completely wrong. There is no way to tell by eye the difference between lab grown and mined unless youre an absolute expert on it. So fellas, you can go up in size and quality by going this route.<//Text>< Pics>

< Text>
I ordered an engagement ring from Yadav and had an excellent experience.  I ordered a 2.22 carat stone with a platinum setting.  Based on my extensive research of the all of the online jewelers, such as James Allen and Blue Nile, I felt Yadav offered a much larger and attractive selection of settings. I was nervous making such a large purchase online, but it all worked out great in the end.  Upon receiving the ring, I took it to a local jeweler to verify it was authentic. <userid>100866558558407039137<//userid>< Text>
Yadav is a honest and responsive business with good diamond and attitude but bad contractor for their rings. Me and my bf are planning to get engaged so I was looking for an engagement diamond online and found one that I like offered by Yadav. A bit on online diamonds: nowadays there's a ton of online diamond website, I think it's basically worth it to get diamonds online cuz the mark-up in physical shops are crazy, but since online diamond stores don't profit that much from their diamonds they may try to make that up by selling slightly over-priced settings. And even among online stores some are more expensive than others, like I think brilliant earth is more expensive than others; the same diamond may get listed on different store's website, like the one I picked was on Yadav and another online store called `with clarity', but Yadav's price is better, so I went with Yadav. Another funny thing is that although Yadav's diamond is cheaper than the other store, the setting is cheaper on the other store's website than Yadav's, so overall the market seems to be quite efficient. So I think the best strategy is to buy the diamond you like from the cheapest website online, and find a local physical jewelry shop to buy a setting. The mistake I made was buying a setting with Yadav: 1) it's expensive: $550 for 18k white gold solitaire setting 2) the first time they gave me a ring of the wrong size and wrong material (14 k instead of 18k) and 3) the second time they did ship me the ring size and material ring, but the diamond is clearly not set in the dead-center of the ring, and the 4 prongs of the ring were not equally spaced, so the ring looked very ugly. But they were super responsive and responsible during the whole process- they always reply email the next day, and they did stand up to what they promised - free return within 30 days with no question asked, and they gave me pre-paid shipping label with insurance on the shipping. I think what happened is that their business model is just to cut cost as much as possible so that they can earn money even when selling diamond at low margin, so they basically find the cheapest contractor out there to make their rings, which means their rings are poor-quality. So I would suggest buying diamond from them but not the ring, and find local jewelry shop to get a ring setting and set the diamond.< /Text>

< Review>
The ring was beautiful and the diamond is great, but there is fire scale/discoloration on the ring after only 5 months. The ring was 18K yellow gold, and the soldered joints are turning a rose gold color. We confirmed with a local jeweler that the ring should not be turning this color; it should've been fused, not soldered. I expressed my disappointment with Yadav, and their response was that the discoloration was due to normal wear and tear (in 5 months!), and offered to polish the ring if we paid $70 to ship it back to them. I replied that the discoloration was not due to normal wear and tear but was in fact due to poor craftsmanship. That email was sent on November 16th, and I have not received a reply, hence this review.

UPDATE 1: I have head back from the owner; they agreed to pay to ship the ring back and check it out, so they have worked to rectify the situation. As such, I have adjusted my rating to 3 stars, and we'll see how the situation gets solved ultimately.

UPDATE 2: After back and forth, I was contacted by the owner, who agreed to pay to ship the ring back. Assumedly, they inspected the setting and determined the setting needed to be replaced. I believe they had a knew one built (although that was never made clear to me) and shipped it back. I believe the process took about 3 weeks.

We are satisfied with the service and my fiance gets compliments on the ring very often. I would recommend Yadav to a purchaser; if there are issues, they will fix them, you just have to stay on them.</Review>

< user>
105906902151339330794<//user>
<username>Joe Charles</username><Date>1523370930712</Date>< rate>
5<//rate>
<text>Yadav was recommended to me by a friend who likes to do meticulous research on things before buying them. I wasn't nervous about buying a diamond online necessarily, but I was unsure of how it would work, since the last time I bought a diamond, I went from store to store looking at loose diamonds until I found the right one.

I called Yadav and they assured me on the phone that they would overnight the diamond, and if it wasn't to my liking, I could just send it back, on their dime. What did I have to lose?

Yadav's website made it very easy to search through many different diamonds at once. You can enter in various search criteria in terms of cost, quality, etc., and then you can look at each actual diamond and its associated GIA report (if applicable). Most came with a full 360-view video, and I found this to be very easy to see any defect/inclusions at different angles.

Once I selected a diamond, it was overnighted to me, double-boxed in a standard large UPS priority box, with no obvious signage on the outside that the box contained anything of significant value. The return address did not even mention that it came from a jewelry store.

In my case, the diamond was exactly what was displayed online, down to every last detail. There were no unexpected surprises. What I saw was what I got, and it was stunning!

Fantastic quality at an amazing price. I am 100% satisfied, and would recommend Yadav to anyone looking for a diamond.</text>< pics>
